			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">This follows on from issue 1198.  Unlike with a Linux toolchain, static and dynamic linking require different linker scripts in the nacl-glibc toolchain.  The default linker script is for dynamic linking.  To test static linking in the Scons build, we pass the (arch-specific) linker script name in manually via &amp;quot;-T&amp;quot;.

Ideally, though, it should be possible to use static linking using &amp;quot;-static&amp;quot; without using &amp;quot;-T&amp;quot;.

This is low priority.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-02-22T22:42:12.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-01-07T09:56:21.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Available</ns2:status><ns2:state>open</ns2:state><ns0:title>nacl-glibc: Make static linking work with "-static" only</ns0:title><ns2:label>Type-Enhancement</ns2:label><ns2:label>Pri-3</ns2:label><ns2:label>Component-GLibC</ns2:label><ns2:label>OS-All</ns2:label><ns2:label>Mstone-X</ns2:label><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/1298/comments/full" rel="replies" type="application/atom+xml" /><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=1298" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/full/1298" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><ns2:stars>1</ns2:stars><ns2:id>1298</ns2:id></ns0:entry>